Part 1

Load data

wf_eco <- read_csv(here::here("data","wildfinder-ecoregions_list.csv"))
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   ecoregion_id = col_character(),
##   ecoregion = col_character(),
##   realm = col_character(),
##   biome = col_character()
## )
wf_ecosp <- read_csv(here::here("data","wildfinder-ecoregions_species.csv"))
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   ecoregion_id = col_character(),
##   species_id = col_double()
## )
wf_sp <- read_csv(here::here("data","wildfinder-mammals_list.csv"))
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   species_id = col_double(),
##   class = col_character(),
##   order = col_character(),
##   family = col_character(),
##   genus = col_character(),
##   species = col_character(),
##   common = col_character(),
##   sci_name = col_character()
## )
wwf <- st_read(here::here("data","wwf_terr_ecos.shp"))
## Reading layer `wwf_terr_ecos' from data source `/media/nschiettekatte/DATA/presentations/datatoolbox/data/wwf_terr_ecos.shp' using driver `ESRI Shapefile'
## Simple feature collection with 14458 features and 21 fields
## geometry type:  POLYGON
## dimension:      XY
## bbox:           xmin: -180 ymin: -89.89197 xmax: 180 ymax: 83.62313
## epsg (SRID):    4326
## proj4string:    +proj=longlat +datum=WGS84 +no_defs
# world object
world <- ne_countries(scale = "medium", returnclass = "sf")

Data wrangling

ursus1 <- wf_sp %>%
  # filter the species
  filter(sci_name == "Ursus arctos") %>%
  # join with wildfinder species and ecoregions
  left_join(wf_ecosp) %>%
  # join with ecoregion info
  left_join(wf_eco) 
## Joining, by = "species_id"
## Joining, by = "ecoregion_id"
wwf_ursus1 <- wwf %>%
  # rename code of ecoregion that has different name in wildfinder and wwf ecoregions
  rename(ecoregion_id = eco_code) %>%
  inner_join(ursus1)
## Joining, by = "ecoregion_id"

Figure 1

Part 2

Wrangle

ursus2 <- wf_sp %>%
  filter(sci_name == "Ursus americanus") %>%
  left_join(wf_ecosp) %>%
  left_join(wf_eco)
## Joining, by = "species_id"
## Joining, by = "ecoregion_id"
wwf_ursus2 <- wwf %>%
  rename(ecoregion_id = eco_code) %>%
  inner_join(ursus2)
## Joining, by = "ecoregion_id"
# use sf to get the intersection of the habitat of two species 
wwf_ursus_overlap <- 
  st_intersection(wwf_ursus1, wwf_ursus2)
## although coordinates are longitude/latitude, st_intersection assumes that they are planar
## Warning: attribute variables are assumed to be spatially constant throughout all
## geometries

Figure 2

ggplot(world) +
  geom_sf() +
  geom_sf(fill = "grey", data = wwf_ursus1) +
  geom_sf(fill = "black", data = wwf_ursus_overlap) +
  theme_minimal() +
  xlab("Longitude") + ylab("Latitude")

Part 3

# transform projection
world2 <- st_transform(world, st_crs("+init=epsg:2163"))

 ggplot(world2) +
   geom_sf() +
   geom_sf(fill = "grey", data = wwf_ursus1) +
   geom_sf(fill = "black", data = wwf_ursus_overlap) +
